2. Use MSTest with `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[DataRow]` for parameterized tests
3. Use Arrange-Act-Assert pattern, name tests as `Method_Condition_ExpectedResult`
4. Test all CRUD actions: happy path, null/missing ID, not-found cases
5. For StudentsController.Index: test sorting (all 4 cases), search filtering, pagination
6. For CoursesController: test file upload validation (invalid extension, file too large), but skip actual file I/O — just test the null-file happy path
7. For DepartmentsController.Edit POST: just test the happy path (concurrency exception is hard to test with InMemory)

8. IMPORTANT: Read the full source code of each controller from disk before writing tests to get exact method signatures and behavior right.

